DOCUMENT();       

loadMacros("PG.pl",
           "PGbasicmacros.pl",
           "PGchoicemacros.pl",
           "PGanswermacros.pl",
           "PGgraphmacros.pl",
           "PGauxiliaryFunctions.pl",
           "PGgraphmacros.pl"
           );
       
TEXT(beginproblem()); # standard preamble to each problem.


$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

$equal = random(4,8,1);
$b = random(800,900,25);
$m = random(40,60,10);

$n = random(100,150,10);
$c = $b - $m * $equal + $n * $equal;

$F = "$b - $m*t";
$A = "$c - $n*t";

BEGIN_TEXT
Question 30:
$BR $SPACE $BR
The cost of a Frigbox refrigerator is ${DOLLAR}$b , and depreciates ${DOLLAR}$m each year.  The cost of an Arctic Air refrigerator is ${DOLLAR}$c , and it depreciates ${DOLLAR}$n per year.
$BR
$BR
a) Find an equation for the value of the Frigbox, $BITALIC F ${EITALIC}, $BITALIC t $EITALIC years after it is purchased.
$BR
$SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE
\( F(t) = \ \) \{ ans_rule(20) \}
$BR
$SPACE
$BR
b) Find an equation for the value of the Arctic Air, $BITALIC A ${EITALIC}, $BITALIC t $EITALIC years after it is purchased.
$BR
$SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE
\( A(t) = \ \) \{ ans_rule(20) \}
$BR
$SPACE
$BR
c) If a Frigbox and an Arctic Air are bought at the same time, when do the two refrigerators have equal value? 
$BR
$SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE
In \{ ans_rule(20) \} $SPACE years.
$BR
END_TEXT

ANS( fun_cmp($F,vars=>'t'));
ANS( fun_cmp($A,vars=>'t'));
ANS( num_cmp($equal) );

$f1 = $c - $b;
$slope = $n - $m;

SOLUTION(EV3(<<'END_SOLUTION'));
$BR $SPACE $BR
$BBOLD SOLUTION $EBOLD
$BR
a)  The equation for $BITALIC F(t) $EITALIC is a line which has slope -$m and $BITALIC F${EITALIC}-intercept $b, so its equation is \( F(t) = $b - $m t \).
$BR $SPACE $BR
b) The equation for $BITALIC A(t) $EITALIC is a line which has slope -$n and $BITALIC F${EITALIC}-intercept $c, so its equation is \( F(t) = $c - $n t \).
$BR $SPACE $BR
c) The two will have the same value when for the same value of $BITALIC t${EITALIC}, \( F(t) = A(t) \):
$BR $SPACE $BR
$SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE 
\( $b - $m t = $c - $n t \)
$BR
$SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE 
\( $slope t = $f1 \)
$BR
$SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE 
\( t = $equal \)
$BR $SPACE $BR
The two will have equal value in $equal years.
$BR
END_SOLUTION
ENDDOCUMENT();   # This should be the last executable line in the problem.